					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm not sure why you're reversing things. Anyway, your code inserts the new bit at the wrong time. You should do the shift before ORing the feedback in, not after.
<br />
<br />BTW, here's a tested direct translation of the <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/APU_Noise" class="postlink">Wiki page</a> to C:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">int other_bit = loop ? 6 : 1;<br />int feedback = &#40;n &amp; 1&#41; ^ &#40;n &gt;&gt; other_bit &amp; 1&#41;;<br />n = n &gt;&gt; 1;<br />n = n | &#40;feedback &lt;&lt; 14&#41;;</div></div>

